The paper deals with lower bounds on communication and randomness complexity of secure multiparty computation, which is a topic in cryptography and information theory (cs.CR, cs.IT). The techniques used in the paper involve data processing inequality and information inequality, which are common in coding theory and communication complexity (cs.CC). The paper also discusses the distribution switching technique, which is related to randomized algorithms and probability theory (cs.DS). Finally, the paper considers the communication and randomness complexity of computing various functions, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
